        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 4:13PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 413 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles southeast of Fort Bidwell, or 17 miles east of Lake City,
moving north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of Modoc and northern
Washoe Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
